# Failure Modes — {{app_slug}}

This file accumulates structured root-cause entries for flows in the `{{app_slug}}` app that have failed in non-trivial ways. The orchestrator surfaces an open entry whose `flow_id` matches a flow about to run, so future runs warn about known traps.

One file per app: `.maestro/qa/failure-modes/{{app_slug}}.md`. Entries are append-only across runs; the installer never rewrites this file once created.

Format per entry:

```
## <flow_id> — <short title>

- Date: <YYYY-MM-DD>
- Status: open | mitigated | resolved
- Symptom: <what was observed>
- Hypothesis: <suspected root cause>
- Repro: <minimal reproduction steps>
- Mitigation: <if any>
- Resolved by: <commit or note>
```

Do not delete this file. The installer preserves entries across runs.
